item.title: Can I use poly pipe for sprinkler system?
item.description: Answer 200 PSI is the maximum pressure that the typical 1″ PVC pipe used for lawn sprinkler systems is rated to endure. Poly pipe of comparable size (1″) is rated to resist 100 PSI. In fact, for polyethylene to attain the same pressure rating as PVC, the walls would need to be twice as thick as those of PVC. Squeeze clamps or saddle fittings are used with poly pipe, and they are not rated.

item.title: Celebrations as new biopiracy treaty agreed at UN
item.description: Representatives of Indigenous peoples celebrated Friday at the United Nations following the agreement of a treaty against the pillaging of their traditional knowledge and genetic resources, like those from medicinal plants. The new treaty, agreed by more than 190 nations, aims to combat so-called biopiracy by making applicants for patents disclose the origins of such materials used in a new invention. Genetic resources -- such as those found in medicinal plants, agricultural crops and animal breeds -- are increasingly used by companies in everything from cosmetics to seeds, medicines, biotechnology and food supplements.

item.title: The Truth About The Ancient Egyptian 'Board Game Of Death'
item.description: This simple game of chance began as a casual activity at the time of its invention, but Egyptologists suspect that around 2300 BCE, the game took on a religious significance with practitioners believing it offered them a conduit to the dead. Think of it like a competitive Ouija board. Contemporaneous Egyptian codices reference the game as a reflection of the soul's movement through Duat, the Egyptian plane of the dead. Archaeological evidence appears to confirm this acquired meaning, as boards from about 1300 BCE onward replaced the basic squares of the early senet boards with hieroglyphic birds associated with the Egyptian soul.

Chemical qualities include such things as flammability, toxicity, acidity, reactivity (of many kinds), and heat of combustion, to name a few. As a result, one can wonder if combustion is a physical or a chemical characteristic. item.title: Ed O'Neill, Rick Moranis and More
item.description: In Little Giants, a motley crew of young football players in Urbania, Ohio, form a team (dubbed Little Giants) to challenge the town's elite pee-wee football team (Urbania Cowboys) for a place at the state playoffs. The elite team is coached by an arrogant ex-football star, Kevin O'Shea (Ed O'Neill), while Kevin's nerdy (and entirely un-athletic) younger brother, Danny O'Shea (Rick Moranis), takes the Little Giants under his wings. A lost bus (and a stroke of luck) result in Coach John Madden and his group of football players (NFL stars Emmitt Smith, Bruce Smith, Tim Brown and Steve Emtman) stumbling across the Little Giants, and they help to get the team ready for the showdown with the Cowboys.
